column2: Number of sequences': where sequences are counted the count should be conducted after quality control UMI processing and replicate/error cloud removal.
Reference genes and alleles' - this is the set of genes and alleles provided to the inference tool.

column3: Identifier of the allele (either IMGT, or the name assigned by the submitter to an inferred gene)
Overall number of sequences assigned to this allele
For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele, as inferred by the tool
For inferred alleles, the closest reference gene and allele that is in the subject's inferred genotype, as inferred by the tool
For inferred alleles, the number of nucleotides that differ between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele

For inferred alleles,  comma-separated list of nucleotide substitutions (e.g. G112A) between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele.  Please use IMGT numbering for V-genes, and number from start of coding sequence for D- or J- genes.
For inferred alleles, the number of amino acids that differ between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele

For inferred alleles, the list of amino acid substitutions (e.g. A96N) between this sequence and the closest reference gene and allele. Please use IMGT numbering for V-genes, and number from start of coding sequence for D- or J- genes.
The number of sequences exactly matching this sequence divided by the number of sequences exactly matching any allele of any gene, *100
The number of records in the sequence dataset exactly matching this unmutated sequence
The number of molecules (identified by Unique Molecular Identifiers) exactly matching this unmutated sequence (if UMIs were used)
The number of sequences exactly matching the sequence of this allele divided by the number of sequences exactly matching any allele of this specific gene, *100
For inferred alleles, the number of D allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) found associated with the inferred sequence
For inferred alleles, the number of J allele calls (i.e., unique allelic sequences) found associated with the inferred sequence
Number of unique CDR3s found associated with an inferred V sequence
For inferred alleles,  the locus (or loci) from which haplotyping was inferred (e.g. IGHJ6)
For inferred alleles, the ratio (expressed as two percentages) with which the two inferred haplotypes were found (e.g. 60:40)
The consensus sequence provided by the inference tool
